comments: Bogdanovic (UTA) brings his arm down and makes contact to the left arm and shoulder of Tate (HOU) that impacts the attempt at the basket.
Porter (HOU) briefly grasps Gobert's (UTA) arm as he moves around the screen.
Porter Jr. (HOU) and Gobert (UTA) engage and disengage in the paint. During the disengage, Porter Jr. extends his arms slightly, and the contact is marginal.
Wood (HOU) briefly brings his arms to the sides of O'Neale (UTA), and the contact is marginal.
Wood (HOU) and Bogdanovic (UTA) engage and separate off-ball.
Wood (HOU) extends his arms out slightly as Gobert (UTA) turns to roll, which doesn't affect his ability to roll to the basket.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Mathews (HOU) and makes marginal contact with Matthews as he rolls to the basket.
Matthews (HOU) establishes himself in a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Ingles (UTA) prior to him returning to the floor.
Gobert (UTA) delivers body contact into Mathews (HOU), which affects his ability to rebound.
Tate (HOU) legally contests Bogdanovic's (UTA) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Conley (UTA) comes from out of bounds and establishes himself inbounds to make a play on the ball. He cleanly dislodges it from Wood (HOU),
Wood (HOU) moves laterally into the path of Bogdanovic (UTA) on the drive, and the contact affects his SQBR.
O'Neale (UTA) legally contests Porter Jr. (HOU) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

Porter Jr. (HOU) slides his hand off Bogdanovic's (UTA) upper body as both players move around the screen, and the contact is marginal. Bogdanovic's reaction is not commensurate with the level of contact.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Wood (HOU) and any contact is marginal.
Conley (UTA) commits a take foul on Mathews (HOU).
After engaging during the screen, Mathews (HOU) momentarily grasps Gobert's (UTA) arm and releases without affecting his FOM.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Mathews (HOU) and absorbs the contact.
During Conley's drive, Porter Jr. (HOU) moves laterally into Conley's (UTA) path and affects his SQBR.
O'Neale (UTA) makes illegal contact to the arm of Mathews (HOU) while attempting to steal the ball.
Conley (UTA) maintains a legal pivot foot prior to releasing his shot.
